title: A United National Concentration list?
face-image: img/events/jxsi_formation.jpg
view-if: true
# view-if: unio_split and next_election_time - time < 9 and next_election_time - time > 3 and (cdc_roadmap > 1 or dl_roadmap > 1 or pdcat_roadmap > 1) and (player_party == "cup" or (player_party == "erc" and (cdc_relations >= 30 or dl_relations >= 30 or pdcat_relations >= 30))) and not consultation_pending and not referendum_pending and not referendum_happened
tags: event
new-page: true
max-visits: 1
go-to: erc_0 if player_party == "erc"; cup_0 if player_party == "cup"
on-arrival: {!
    // TODO: Remove, just for testing!!
    Q.year = 2015;
    Q.month = 7;
    Q.unio_split = true;
    Q.cdc_parlament_s = Math.ceil(0.75*Q.ciu_parlament_s);
    Q.unio_parlament_s = Math.floor(0.25*Q.ciu_parlament_s);
    Q.ciu_parlament_s = 0;
    Q.cdc_leader = Q.ciu_leader;
    Q.cdc_leader_gender = Q.ciu_leader_gender;
    Q.cdc_roadmap = 2;
    Q.cat_coalition = ["cdc"];
    Q.cat_coalition_disp = "CDC <span style='font-style: italic'>caretaker gov.</span>"
    Q.president_party = "CDC";

    for (var c of Q.parlament_constituencies) {
        for (var d of Q.parlament_demographics) {
            Q["cdc_parlament_" + c + "_" + d + "_support"] = 0.8 * Q["ciu_parlament_" + c + "_" + d + "_support"];
            Q["ciu_parlament_" + c + "_" + d + "_support"] = 0;
        }
    }
!}


# TODO: united_bcn_local and united_congreso options a few months past the event? or via card???
# TODO: actual jxsi cards

= A United National Concentration list?

[? if consultation_happened: After the very questionable outcome of the non-binding consultation, ?][? if not consultation_happened: After this a legislature defined by debates on independence, ?][? if cdc_parlament_s > 0: CDC leader [+ cdc_leader +]?][? if dl_parlament_s > 0: DL leader [+ dl_leader +]?][? if pdcat_parlament_s > 0: PDeCAT leader [+ pdcat_leader +]?] is now openly proposing something truly unheard of. A National concentration list for the upcoming elections, agglutinating the main pro-independence parties into a single, unified candidacy. This umbrella, jxsi, would be opened widely to include profiles from the civil society: local and Catalan-wide leaders and organizers of the independence movement, jumping into parliamentary and party politics to focus on self-determination and building the insitutional apparatus necessary for independence. All with a very ambitious timeline: 18 months from the elections to a referendum, which should lead to a declaration of independence, a constituent process and ultimately to Catalan Republic.

While the proposal is exciting for many, it is also a big ask. The collaboration left-to-right bridge between ERC and [? if cdc_parlament_s > 0: CDC?][? if dl_parlament_s > 0: DL?][? if pdcat_parlament_s > 0: the PDeCAT?] is indeed sustained precisely by national interests, and that has naturally never been enough to convince everyone in either party. 

@erc_0
on-arrival: {!
    Q.jxsi_formation_erc_leverage = 0;
    const _activeCiu = Q.cdc_parlament_s > 0 ? "cdc" : Q.dl_parlament_s > 0 ? "dl" : "pdcat";
    for (var c of Q.parlament_constituencies) {
        var erc_votes = 0;
        var ciu_votes = 0;
        for (var d of Q.parlament_demographics) {
            erc_votes = Q["erc_parlament_" + c + "_" + d+ "_support"] * Q["parlament_" + c + "_" + d + "_pop"];
            ciu_votes = Q[_activeCiu + "_parlament_" + c + "_" + d+ "_support"] * Q["parlament_" + c + "_" + d + "_pop"];
        }
        if (erc_votes >= ciu_votes) {
            Q.jxsi_formation_erc_leverage += 1;
        }
    }
    if (Q[_activeCiu + "_relations"] > 65) {
        Q.jxsi_formation_erc_leverage += 1;
    }
    if (Q.erc_parlament_s >= Q.ciu_parlament_s * 0.85) {
        Q.jxsi_formation_erc_leverage += 1;
    }
    // TODO: Other forms of leverage win for erc??
!}

The biggest point of contention, of course, is leadership and party splitting of the coalition. Traditionally dominant [? if cdc_parlament_s > 0: CDC?][? if dl_parlament_s > 0: DL?][? if pdcat_parlament_s > 0: PDeCAT?] is pushing to maintain its dominance, but we *may* have some wiggle room. We can always refuse such an alliance, even if that may disappoint many.

- @erc_40
- @erc_50
- @erc_60
- @erc_no

@erc_40
title: [? if cdc_parlament_s > 0: CDC's candidate, [+ cdc_leader +]?][? if dl_parlament_s > 0: DL's candidate, [+ dl_leader +]?][? if pdcat_parlament_s > 0: PDeCAT's candidate, [+ pdcat_leader +]?] shall lead
subtitle: The formal split will be 40 - 60 between ERC and [? if cdc_parlament_s > 0: CDC?][? if dl_parlament_s > 0: DL?][? if pdcat_parlament_s > 0: PDeCAT?]
face-image: img/events/jxsi_mas.jpg
on-arrival: {!
    Q.jxsi_formation_num = 45;
    const _activeCiu = Q.cdc_parlament_s > 0 ? "cdc" : Q.dl_parlament_s > 0 ? "dl" : "pdcat";
    Q.jxsi_leader = Q[_activeCiu + "_leader"];
    Q.jxsi_leader_gender = Q[_activeCiu + "_leader_gender"];
!}
go-to: erc_jxsi_formation


